hopobject.body: Would you like to leave a message? can someone recommend a good online pharmacy Nothing sums up better the Scotch egg's spectacular fall from grace. Once upon a time, this confection of rich yolky egg and breadcrumbed sausagemeat was a glorious British treat – the kind enjoyed by wealthy Victorians at picnics, or scoffed gleefully by Enid Blyton’s Famous Five as they ran headlong into another politically incorrect adventure. Fastforward to the 1990s however, and suddenly the Scotch egg was a stale disappointment that seemed to lurk solely in petrol stations - though even then you’d only buy one if there weren’t any Ginster's pork pies left on the shelf.
